<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-26T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-26T15:00:00-05:00" n="153" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d153">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/9719</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Droppers</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-26T22:00:00+02:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1918, 10 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 27, 9.15
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>488. Your 429, April 19, 5 p.m. Have given publicity to statement in
                                your telegram. It has had happy and widespread effect. <persName corresp="#p_VEK1">Venizelos</persName> said to me a month ago he
                                would like some assurance from Entente Powers about integrity of
                                Greece, if not publicly then privately, so that he could if
                                challenged in the House of Representatives reassure the members.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_DG1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Droppers</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>